Adriano Malori.label: Adriano Malori
Adriano Malori.description: Adriano Malori is an Italian professional road racing cyclist, who currently rides for UCI ProTeam Movistar Team. Malori was the Lanterne Rouge of the 2010 Tour de France, finishing almost four and a half hours behind winner Andy Schleck. Wikipedia

Aitor Galdós.label: Aitor Galdós
Aitor Galdós.description: Aitor Galdós Alonso is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer for UCI Professional Continental team Caja Rural-Seguros RGA. Wikipedia

Albert Richter.label: Albert Richter
Albert Richter.description: Albert Richter was a German cyclist who won the world sprint championship. He was taken from a train by the Gestapo and never seen alive again. Wikipedia

Albert Van Damme.label: Albert Van Damme
Albert Van Damme.description: Albert "Berten" Van Damme is a former Belgian cyclo-crosser. He won 109 individual races, became six times Belgian National Champion and once World Champion, in 1974. His career lasted from 1959 till 1978. Wikipedia

Alexander Efimkin.label: Alexander Efimkin
Alexander Efimkin.description: Alexander Alexandrovich Efimkin is a Russian professional road bicycle racer for UCI Professional Continental team Team Novo Nordisk. His twin brother is Vladimir Efimkin. Wikipedia

Anthony Delaplace.label: Anthony Delaplace
Anthony Delaplace.description:
Anthony Delaplace is a professional French road cyclist, currently riding for Bretagne-Séché Environnement.
Delaplace was a junior champion for France in 2007. Wikipedia

Artem Ovechkin.label: Artem Ovechkin
Artem Ovechkin.description: Artem Ovechkin is a Russian professional road bicycle racer who rides for UCI Professional Continental Team RusVelo. Wikipedia

Bas Giling.label: Bas Giling
Bas Giling.description:
Bastiaan "Bas" Giling is a Dutch professional road bicycle racer for UCI Continental team Team Designa Køkken, having previously ridden for UCI ProTour T-Mobile Team.
Giling is the cousin of cyclists Matthé Pronk and Jos Pronk. Wikipedia

Bernd Dittert.label: Bernd Dittert
Bernd Dittert.description: Bernd Dittert is a retired racing cyclist from East Germany, who won the bronze medal for his native country in the men's 4,000m individual pursuit at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul, South Korea. Wikipedia

Ben Swift.label: Ben Swift
Ben Swift.description: Benjamin "Ben" Swift is an English professional track and road racing cyclist who rides for Team Sky, and has been with the team since 2010. Swift won the scratch race at the 2012 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. Wikipedia

Bert De Waele.label: Bert De Waele
Bert De Waele.description: Bert De Waele is a Belgian retired professional road racing cyclist, who competed as a professional between 2001 and 2012. He spent his entire career with the Landbouwkrediet-Colnago team through various iterations of team names. Wikipedia

Blel Kadri.label: Blel Kadri
Blel Kadri.description: Blel Kadri is a French professional road racing cyclist, who currently rides for UCI ProTeam Ag2r-La Mondiale. Wikipedia

Bruno Risi.label: Bruno Risi
Bruno Risi.description:
Bruno Risi is a Swiss professional racing cyclist.
He is the ninth Swiss sportsperson to compete at five Olympics, after middle-distance runner Paul Martin, equestrians Henri Chammartin and Gustav ... Wikipedia

Bradley McGee.label: Bradley McGee
Bradley McGee.description: Bradley John McGee OAM is an Australian former professional racing cyclist. He is currently the head coach of the New South Wales Institute of Sport. He started cycling in 1986 at the age of ten. He lives in Sydney and in Nice, France. Wikipedia

Cameron Meyer.label: Cameron Meyer
Cameron Meyer.description: Cameron Meyer is an Australian professional racing cyclist, riding for UCI ProTeam Orica-GreenEDGE. Born in Viveash, Western Australia, Meyer started cycling at the age of 13 in 2001 and first represented ... Wikipedia

Chris Hoy.label: Chris Hoy
Chris Hoy.description: Sir Christopher Andrew "Chris" Hoy, MBE is a British former track cyclist who represented Great Britain at the Olympics and World Championships and Scotland at the Commonwealth Games. Hoy considers himself to be both Scottish and British. Wikipedia
Awards: BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award
National Television Award for Landmark Achievement

Chris Witty.label: Chris Witty
Chris Witty.description:
Christine Diane "Chris" Witty is an American speed skater and racing cyclist and participated in the Olympic Games in both sports.
She won medals at both 1000 and 1500 meters in the 1998 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia
Chris Witty.Born: June 23, 1975 (age 38), West Allis, Wisconsin, United States

Christophe Capelle.label: Christophe Capelle
Christophe Capelle.description:
Christophe Capelle is a French former racing cyclist.
Capelle won a gold medal for France in the 4000-meter team pursuit at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, riding alongside Philippe Ermenault, Jean-Michel Monin, and Francis Moreau. Wikipedia

Daniel Navarro.label: Daniel Navarro
Daniel Navarro.description: Daniel Navarro García is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer for UCI Professional Continental Team Cofidis. Wikipedia

Daniel Oss.label: Daniel Oss
Daniel Oss.description: Daniel Oss is an Italian professional road bicycle racer who is currently racing with American BMC Racing Team, on the UCI ProTour. Wikipedia

David de la Fuente.label: David de la Fuente
David de la Fuente.description: David de la Fuente Rasilla is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer. He rides for the Torku Şeker Spor cycling team, having left Caja Rural after the 2012 season. Wikipedia

Denis Galimzyanov.label: Denis Galimzyanov
Denis Galimzyanov.description: Denis Ramilievitch Galimzyanov is a Russian racing cyclist, who last rode for UCI ProTeam Team Katusha. He obtained a major victory in the classic Paris–Brussels in 2011, where he imposed himself in a massive sprint after 218.5 kilometers of racing. Wikipedia

Davide Cassani.label: Davide Cassani
Davide Cassani.description:
Davide Cassani is a former road cyclist from Italy. He now works as a cycling commentator on Italian television.
He was born in Faenza. In 1982 he made his professional debut with Termolan-Galli. Wikipedia

Dominique Cornu.label: Dominique Cornu
Dominique Cornu.description: Dominique Cornu is a Belgian road and track cyclist from Flanders, currently riding for UCI Continental team Sunweb-Napoleon Games. He specializes in the time trial discipline. Wikipedia

Dries Devenyns.label: Dries Devenyns
Dries Devenyns.description:
Dries Devenyns is a Belgian professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTeam Giant-Shimano.
Devenyns left Omega Pharma-Quick Step at the end of the 2013 season, after five seasons with the squad, and joined Giant-Shimano for 2014. Wikipedia

Edoardo Molinar.label: Edoardo Molinar
Edoardo Molinar.description:
Edoardo Molinar was an Italian cyclist.
He was a professional cyclist in 1931-1948, except for Second World War's years.
He was a winner of Puy-de-Dôme and 13th stage of 1935 Vuelta a España, the 1st edition of this competition. Wikipedia

Eric Baumann (cyclist).label: Eric Baumann
Eric Baumann (cyclist).description: Eric Baumann is a German professional road bicycle racer for Team NetApp in 2010 and used to ride for the UCI Continental team Team Sparkasse. Wikipedia

Erki Pütsep.label: Erki Pütsep
Erki Pütsep.description: Erki Pütsep is an Estonian professional road bicycle racer who rides for the Alpha Baltic-Unitymarathons.com team. He is the three time national road race champion and won the E.O.S. Tallinn GP in 2007. Wikipedia

Fabio Felline.label: Fabio Felline
Fabio Felline.description:
Fabio Felline is an Italian professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTeam Trek Factory Racing.
In 2010, Felline took the start of his first Tour de France for Footon-Servetto-Fuji. He was the youngest competitor in that year's Tour. Wikipedia

Fabio Taborre.label: Fabio Taborre
Fabio Taborre.description: Fabio Taborre is a professional Italian road cyclist, currently riding for Yellow Fluo. Wikipedia

Filippo Savini.label: Filippo Savini
Filippo Savini.description: Filippo Savini is an Italian professional road bicycle racer for UCI Continental team Ceramica Flaminia-Fondriest. Wikipedia

Florent Brard.label: Florent Brard
Florent Brard.description: Florent Brard is a retired French road bicycle racer. He won three national championships, including the professional road race. He became a professional in 1999 and stopped racing in November 2009 after not finding a place in a team. Wikipedia

Frédéric Moncassin.label: Frédéric Moncassin
Frédéric Moncassin.description:
Frédéric Moncassin is a French former road racing cyclist. He turned professional in 1990 and retired in 1999.
Moncassin was a strong roadman-sprinter known for his tussles with other riders in the last metres of a race. Wikipedia

Freddy Bichot.label: Freddy Bichot
Freddy Bichot.description:
Freddy Bichot is a French road racing cyclist who rides for Véranda Rideau-Super U.
After rising from relative obscurity, in 2002 he won the French Amateur National Championship, yet later tested positive for testosterone. Wikipedia

Frederik Veuchelen.label: Frederik Veuchelen
Frederik Veuchelen.description: Frederik Veuchelen is a Belgian professional road bicycle racer for UCI Professional Continental team Wanty-Groupe Gobert. Wikipedia

Gabriele Bosisio.label: Gabriele Bosisio
Gabriele Bosisio.description: Gabriele Bosisio is an Italian professional road bicycle racer. Bosisio rode for Tenax between 2003 and 2005 and for UCI Professional Continental team LPR Brakes-Ballan between 2008 and 2009. Wikipedia

Gerrit Glomser.label: Gerrit Glomser
Gerrit Glomser.description: Gerrit Glomser is an Austrian racing cyclist with Team Volksbank. He turned professional in 1998. Wikipedia

Giuliano Figueras.label: Giuliano Figueras
Giuliano Figueras.description: Giuliano Figueras is an Italian former professional road bicycle racer. He turned professional in 1998 with Mapei team and won a stage of the Tour de Langkawi that year. In 1999 and 2000 Figueras had 7 wins including a stage of the Giro di Romandia. Wikipedia

Grega Bole.label: Grega Bole
Grega Bole.description: Grega Bole is a Slovenian professional road bicycle racer, who last rode for UCI ProTeam Vacansoleil-DCM. His biggest victory is the 2011 GP Ouest-France, where he launched a solo attach with 2 kilometres to go. Wikipedia

Guido Fulst.label: Guido Fulst
Guido Fulst.description: Guido Fulst is a German racing cyclist, who competed for the SG Dynamo Wernigerode, SC Dynamo Berlin/ Sportvereinigung Dynamo. He won many titles during his career. Wikipedia

Hanka Kupfernagel.label: Hanka Kupfernagel
Hanka Kupfernagel.description: Hanka Kupfernagel is a German professional cycle racer. Currently her primary focus is cyclocross racing, however, she has won major road, track and mountain bike races. Wikipedia

Hayden Roulston.label: Hayden Roulston
Hayden Roulston.description: Hayden Roulston, MNZM is a New Zealand professional racing cyclist for UCI ProTour team Trek Factory Racing. Wikipedia

Hendrik Van Dijck.label: Hendrik Van Dijck
Hendrik Van Dijck.description: Hendrik Van Dijck is a Belgian former professional road bicycle racer. Wikipedia

Iban Mayoz.label: Iban Mayoz
Iban Mayoz.description: Iban Mayoz Exteberria is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer, currently not under contract to any team. He began his career at Relax in 2004 before moving to ProTour team Euskaltel-Euskadi in 2006, and then to Karpin-Galicia in 2008. Wikipedia

Jérémie Galland.label: Jérémie Galland
Jérémie Galland.description: Jérémie Galland is a French former professional road cyclist, who competed as a professional between 2007 and 2013. Wikipedia

Jan Bárta.label: Jan Bárta
Jan Bárta.description: Jan Bárta is a professional Czech road cyclist, currently riding for Team NetApp-Endura. Wikipedia

Jan Bakelants.label: Jan Bakelants
Jan Bakelants.description: Jan Bakelants is a Belgian professional road bicycle racer for the Omega Pharma-Quick Step team. His major wins include the 2008 Tour de l'Avenir and stage 2 of the 2013 Tour de France, claiming the yellow jersey. Wikipedia

Jan Schaffrath.label: Jan Schaffrath
Jan Schaffrath.description: Jan Schaffrath is a German directeur sportif for UCI ProTeam Omega Pharma-Quick Step and former professional road bicycle racer. Before turning professional he was twice military World Champion. Wikipedia

Jean-Christophe Péraud.label: Jean-Christophe Péraud
Jean-Christophe Péraud.description: Jean-Christophe Péraud is a French cyclist and was a member of the French team at the 2008 and 2012 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Jean-Patrick Nazon.label: Jean-Patrick Nazon
Jean-Patrick Nazon.description:
Jean-Patrick Nazon is a French professional road bicycle racer who turned professional in 1997.
2 stages, Circuit des Mines
2 stages, Étoile de Bessèges
Stage, Critérium International
Stage, Four Days ... Wikipedia

Jens Keukeleire.label: Jens Keukeleire
Jens Keukeleire.description: Jens Keukeleire is a professional road racing cyclist currently riding for UCI ProTeam Orica-GreenEDGE. Wikipedia

Jesús Montoya.label: Jesús Montoya
Jesús Montoya.description: Jesús Montoya Alarcon is a Spanish former road bicycle racer. Wikipedia

Joanna Rowsell.label: Joanna Rowsell
Joanna Rowsell.description: Joanna Katie Rowsell MBE is an English cyclist on the Great Britain Cycling Team who competes on track and road. Wikipedia

John Talen.label: John Talen
John Talen.description: John Talen is a former road racing cyclist from the Netherlands, who was a professional from 1987 to 2000. Wikipedia

Johnny Hoogerland.label: Johnny Hoogerland
Johnny Hoogerland.description: Johnny Hoogerland is a Dutch professional cyclist riding for the Italian Androni Giocattoli-Venezuela team. Due to the prominent bull-tattoo on his arm and his roots from the peninsula of Zuid-Beveland he is nicknamed the "Bull of Beveland". Wikipedia

Jonas Ljungblad.label: Jonas Ljungblad
Jonas Ljungblad.description: Jonas Ljungblad is a Swedish road racing cyclist, currently riding for Team Differdange-Losch. He began his professional career with the Amore & Vita team in 2002 as a young helper but after spending ... Wikipedia

Jonathan Monsalve.label: Jonathan Monsalve
Jonathan Monsalve.description: Jonathan Monsalve is a professional Venezuelan road cyclist, currently riding for UCI Professional Continental team Yellow Fluo. Wikipedia

Jonathan Tiernan-Locke.label: Jonathan Tiernan-Locke
Jonathan Tiernan-Locke.description: Jonathan Tiernan-Locke is a British professional road racing cyclist who rides for UCI ProTeam Team Sky. Tiernan-Locke's major breakthrough came from winning four stage races during the 2012 UCI Europe Tour, including the Tour of Britain. Wikipedia

Joost van Leijen.label: Joost van Leijen
Joost van Leijen.description: Joost van Leijen is a Dutch former professional road cyclist, who competed as a professional between 2010 and 2013. Wikipedia

José Alberto Benítez.label: José Alberto Benítez
José Alberto Benítez.description: José Alberto Benítez Roman is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer, who last rode with UCI Professional Continental team Andalucía-Caja Granada. Wikipedia

José Antonio Hermida.label: José Antonio Hermida
José Antonio Hermida.description: José Antonio Hermida Ramos is a Spanish cyclist of Galician origin specializing in competitive mountain biking. He won the silver medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece after having finished in fourth place in the 2000 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Julien Absalon.label: Julien Absalon
Julien Absalon.description: Julien Absalon is a French cross-country mountain biker. He won consecutive gold medals at the 2004 Summer Olympics and at the 2008 Summer Olympics. At the 2012 Summer Olympics cross-country race, he suffered a tyre puncture in the opening lap. Wikipedia
Nominations: Laureus World Sports Award for Action Sportsperson of the Year

Kevyn Ista.label: Kevyn Ista
Kevyn Ista.description: Kevyn Ista is a Belgian road bicycle racer who rides for UCI Professional Continental team IAM Cycling. In 2012, he rode for Accent.jobs-Willems Veranda's. Wikipedia

Koen de Kort.label: Koen de Kort
Koen de Kort.description: Koen de Kort is a Dutch professional cyclist. Born in Gouda, De Kort grew up in Liempde in Noord Brabant. From 2002 to 2004, he was in the development team of the Rabobank cycling team. Wikipedia

Marianne Vos.label: Marianne Vos
Marianne Vos.description: Marianne Vos, is a Dutch cyclo-cross, road bicycle racer and track racer who has drawn comparison to Eddy Merckx as being "the finest cyclist of [her] generation". Wikipedia

Koos Moerenhout.label: Koos Moerenhout
Koos Moerenhout.description: Jacobus Moerenhout is a Dutch former professional road bicycle racer. Wikipedia

Koldo Gil.label: Koldo Gil
Koldo Gil.description: Koldo Gil Pérez is a Spanish professional road racing cyclist, currently riding for the UCI Continental team Liberty Seguros Continental. Wikipedia

Luca Gelfi.label: Luca Gelfi
Luca Gelfi.description: Luca Gelfi was an Italian racing cyclist. Gelfi suffered from depression and committed suicide in 2009 Wikipedia

Mario Kummer.label: Mario Kummer
Mario Kummer.description: Mario Kummer is a retired track and road racing cyclist from East Germany, who represented his native country at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul, South Korea. Wikipedia

Marshall Taylor.label: Marshall Taylor
Marshall Taylor.description: Marshall Walter "Major" Taylor was an American cyclist who won the world 1 mile track cycling championship in 1899 after setting numerous world records and overcoming racial discrimination. Wikipedia

Massimo Podenzana.label: Massimo Podenzana
Massimo Podenzana.description: Massimo Podenzana is an Italian former road racing cyclist. Podenzana won stages in both the Giro d'Italia, and the Tour de France, as well as a verity of other cycling classics. Wikipedia

Mathieu Cordang.label: Mathieu Cordang
Mathieu Cordang.description: Mathieu Cordang was a Dutch professional cyclist. Cordang's specialties were track racing and endurance racing. Wikipedia

Mathieu Ladagnous.label: Mathieu Ladagnous
Mathieu Ladagnous.description: Mathieu Ladagnous is a French road racing cyclist who rides for FDJ.fr. He also competes as a track cyclist. Wikipedia

Matteo Montaguti.label: Matteo Montaguti
Matteo Montaguti.description: Matteo Montaguti is a professional Italian racing cyclist, currently riding for Ag2r-La Mondiale. Wikipedia

Matteo Rabottini.label: Matteo Rabottini
Matteo Rabottini.description: Matteo Rabottini is an Italian racing cyclist with UCI Professional Continental team Yellow Fluo. Wikipedia

Maxime Bouet.label: Maxime Bouet
Maxime Bouet.description: Maxime Bouet is a French road racing cyclist who rides for UCI ProTour team Ag2r-La Mondiale. Wikipedia

Michel Kreder.label: Michel Kreder
Michel Kreder.description: Michel Kreder is a Dutch professional racing cyclist who rides for Wanty-Groupe Gobert. His cousin Wesley, also rides for Wanty-Groupe Gobert; Kreder's younger brother Raymond is also a professional cyclist, and rides for Garmin-Sharp. Wikipedia

Ole Ritter.label: Ole Ritter
Ole Ritter.description: Ole Ritter is a former Danish racing cyclist, mainly known for breaking the hour record in 1968. Wikipedia

Oscar Gatto.label: Oscar Gatto
Oscar Gatto.description: Oscar Gatto is an Italian racing cyclist with UCI ProTeam Cannondale. He is often called and therefore his nickname is 'Oscar the Cat' because his surname when translated from Italian to English is Cat. Wikipedia

Paolo Lanfranchi.label: Paolo Lanfranchi
Paolo Lanfranchi.description: Paolo Lanfranchi is a retired Italian professional road bicycle racer. Originally from Gazzaniga, Italy. Lanfranchi has been a dominating figure in the Italian road racing scene by winning many points standings. Wikipedia

Per Pedersen (cyclist).label: Per Pedersen
Per Pedersen (cyclist).description: Per Pedersen is a retired road bicycle racer from Denmark, who was a professional rider from 1986 to 1993. He competed in four Tours de France. Today he runs a bicycle shop near Herning, Denmark. Wikipedia

Paolo Tiralongo.label: Paolo Tiralongo
Paolo Tiralongo.description:
Paolo Tiralongo is an Italian professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTour team Astana.
In 2009, while riding for Lampre-NGC, Tiralongo registered his best final result on a Grand Tour, finishing ... Wikipedia

Peter Wrolich.label: Peter Wrolich
Peter Wrolich.description: Peter Wrolich is a retired Austrian professional road bicycle racer. He was known as a sprinter. He was in the top 10 of the last stage of the 2006 Tour de France, with a total of 65 points. Wikipedia

Pierre Rolland (cyclist).label: Pierre Rolland
Pierre Rolland (cyclist).description: Pierre Rolland is a French professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTeam Team Europcar. Wikipedia

Petra Rossner.label: Petra Rossner
Petra Rossner.description: Petra Rossner is a German cyclist, who won the gold medal in 3 km pursuit track cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona. In the same event she won the 1991 World Championships and finished second in 1989. Wikipedia

Rémy Di Gregorio.label: Rémy Di Gregorio
Rémy Di Gregorio.description: Rémy Di Gregorio is a French road bicycle racer, who rides for UCI Continental Team La Pomme Marseille 13. He has previously competed professionally for Cofidis in 2012, after moving from Astana after the 2011 season. Wikipedia

Rafael Antonio Niño.label: Rafael Antonio Niño
Rafael Antonio Niño.description: Rafael Antonio Niño Munévar is a retired Colombian road racing cyclist. He won the Vuelta a Colombia in 1970. After that he became a professional cyclist from 1973 to 1974. He participated in the Giro d'Italia. Wikipedia

Robert Kišerlovski.label: Robert Kišerlovski
Robert Kišerlovski.description: Robert Kišerlovski is a Croatian professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTeam Trek Factory Racing. He turned professional in 2005. Wikipedia

Rick Flens.label: Rick Flens
Rick Flens.description: Rick Flens is a Dutch professional road bicycle racer for UCI ProTeam Belkin Pro Cycling. Wikipedia

Ramūnas Navardauskas.label: Ramūnas Navardauskas
Ramūnas Navardauskas.description: Ramūnas Navardauskas is a Lithuanian professional road racing cyclist who rides for UCI ProTeam Garmin-Sharp. After four years in the amateur ranks, Navardauskas turned professional in 2011 with the Garmin-Cervélo team. Wikipedia

Rodolfo Massi.label: Rodolfo Massi
Rodolfo Massi.description: Rodolfo Massi is an Italian former professional road bicycle racer. He won a stage in 1996 Giro d'Italia and 1998 Tour de France, but was expelled from the 1998 Tour de France after illegal doping was found in his hotel room. Wikipedia

Rolf Aldag.label: Rolf Aldag
Rolf Aldag.description: Rolf Aldag is a former professional road bicycle racer who rode for Team Telekom from 1993 to 2005. He raced in 10 Tour de France, 1 Giro d'Italia and 5 Vuelta a España. Prior to joining Telekom, he raced with Helvetia. Wikipedia

Rubens Bertogliati.label: Rubens Bertogliati
Rubens Bertogliati.description: Rubens Bertogliati is a Swiss retired road racing cyclist, whose breakthrough came in the 2002 Tour de France, when he was riding for the Italian Lampre-Daikin team. Wikipedia

Salvatore Commesso.label: Salvatore Commesso
Salvatore Commesso.description:
Salvatore Commesso is an Italian professional road bicycle racer who most recently rode for UCI Professional Continental team Preti Mangimi.
He was born in Torre del Greco, Campania, and turned professional in 1998. Wikipedia

Leonardo Sierra.label: Leonardo Sierra
Leonardo Sierra.description: Leonardo Sierra Sepúlveda is a Venezuelan former road bicycle racer. Wikipedia

Sarah Ulmer.label: Sarah Ulmer
Sarah Ulmer.description: Sarah Ulmer, ONZM is the first New Zealander to win an Olympic cycling gold medal, which she won in the individual pursuit at the 2004 Olympics in Athens, setting a world record. Wikipedia

Stefan van Dijk.label: Stefan van Dijk
Stefan van Dijk.description:
Stefan van Dijk is a former professional road racing cyclist.
In November 2013, van Dijk announced his retirement from professional cycling, after fourteen seasons. Wikipedia
